#[navbar]

#[section, $md:
    @../ (Documentation) / Memory and lifetimes

    # Memory and lifetimes

    Beanstalk is reference-semantic by default, copy-explicit and move-inferred. Existing values use shared read-only access. Mutation requires explicit exclusive access. Copies are explicit and moves are inferred by the compiler.

    These pages cover source-facing memory behaviour. For the formal memory model, borrow validation and backend lowering, see @../../codebase/memory-management (Memory management).
]

